From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] sky2: force Baikal GBE chip_id when hw reports 0x0

After patch 0003 made the PHY-reset and probe-time IF blocks include
Baikal alongside Aeolia, sky2_probe still aborts in sky2_init() with:

    sky2 0000:00:14.1: unsupported chip type 0x0
    sky2 0000:00:14.1: probe with driver sky2 failed with error -95

The B2_CHIP_ID register on Sony's Baikal GBE silicon (0x90d8) returns
0x00 instead of one of the documented YUKON family IDs. The
sky2_init() switch on chip_id therefore falls into the `default` case
and bails -EOPNOTSUPP.

Aeolia GBE 0x909e reports CHIP_ID_YUKON_FE_P; Belize GBE 0x90c9 reports
the same family. Baikal silicon is otherwise functionally compatible,
so override chip_id to YUKON_PRM (newest documented family) when the
register reports 0x0 and the device is the Sony Baikal GBE. Gated on
hw->chip_id == 0 — if a future Baikal revision starts reporting a real
chip ID, this becomes a no-op.

This is the second half of "treat Baikal like Aeolia for sky2" —
patch 0003 covered the conditional code paths; this covers the
chip-type detection that runs first.

Reference: rmuxnet/ps4-linux-12xx never resolved this on the
ps4-baikal-ethernet-experiment branch (846b0b28 only covered the same
surface as our patch 0003). Chip-id override is original to this tree.
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/sky2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/sky2.c
@@ -3137,6 +3137,18 @@
 	sky2_write8(hw, B0_CTST, CS_RST_CLR);

 	hw->chip_id = sky2_read8(hw, B2_CHIP_ID);
+#ifdef CONFIG_X86_PS4
+	if (hw->chip_id == 0 &&
+	    hw->pdev->vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_SONY &&
+	    hw->pdev->device == PCI_DEVICE_ID_SONY_BAIKAL_GBE) {
+		/* Sony Baikal GBE reports 0x00 on B2_CHIP_ID. The chip is
+		 * functionally compatible with the Yukon-PRM family used in
+		 * Aeolia/Belize variants. Force the family so the switch
+		 * below finds a matching case. */
+		dev_info(&hw->pdev->dev, "PS4 Baikal: B2_CHIP_ID=0x0, forcing YUKON_PRM\n");
+		hw->chip_id = CHIP_ID_YUKON_PRM;
+	}
+#endif
 	hw->chip_rev = (sky2_read8(hw, B2_MAC_CFG) & CFG_CHIP_R_MSK) >> 4;

 	switch (hw->chip_id) {
